															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1814684&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610164672" alt="GreenWolf" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1814684)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;" >GreenWolf</a></span> <span class="odate time_1449268599 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">04 Dec 2015 22:36</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2417692">
									

<p>Most of this proposal is entirely plausible under current physics, if many hundreds of years beyond our current tech level. For those curious about the finer details of constructing a black hole powered starship, I refer you to <a href="http://arxiv.org/pdf/0908.1803v1.pdf">this</a> paper, which was an invaluable reference during the writing of this article. It's a shame that I couldn't use it as one of the citations in-universe due to its publishing date in 2009.</p>
<p>The object accelerating towards Earth, PSR B0531+21, is <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">SCP-1548</span> a skip that no longer exists.</p>
<p>Thanks go out to the following people for helping critique and review this: <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tygently" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2038009); return false;">TyGently</a></span>, <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/twistedgears" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1735681); return false;">TwistedGears</a></span>, <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/decibelles" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2005044); return false;">Decibelles</a></span>, <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/doctor-cimmerian" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1414765); return false;">Doctor Cimmerian</a></span>, <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/minmin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(560062); return false;">minmin</a></span>, <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-leonard" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1798567); return false;">Dr Leonard</a></span>, <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/randomini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1379080); return false;">Randomini</a></span>, <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tahunu" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1557546); return false;">tahunu</a></span>, Dr Gravity, <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;">MrWrong</a></span>, <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;">sirpudding</a></span>, and various other members of #site19. If I missed your name, feel free to give me a poke and I'll add you to the list.</p>
<p>The diagram used for Figure A is my own work, which I am releasing under CC-BY-SA 3.0. It was created as a .svg in Inkscape, and then exported as a .png.</p>

