					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/arcuriel" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2226362); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2226362&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610164672" alt="Arcuriel" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2226362)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/arcuriel" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2226362); return false;" >Arcuriel</a></span> <span class="odate time_1449286888 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">05 Dec 2015 03:41</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2417790">
									

<p>Very nice. I love how the anomalous technology is there, but more in a supporting role, so that we can still get some idea of how the vessel would operate with regular physics.</p>
<p>Is it just me, or does this grant request sound like it was written as a cool idea by an excited employee, who then searched around for some justification for going ahead with it? That's not a bad thing at all, if so, just wondering if that was at all the intention.</p>
<p>$2 billion sounds a bit low of a cost to me, but 1. I don't actually know how much a space ship actually costs, and 2. Prometheus Labs almost certainly has 'paratechnology' that would let them cut costs in one way or another.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;bad&nbsp;pun</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>On a less serious note,</p>
<blockquote>
<p>A Randall detector, used to detect high-energy particles indicative of inter-universal travel.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Wouldn't a Randall detector be used to locate raptors?</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Overall, +1.</p>

							</div>

								
					
